cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper investigates the performance of distributional semantic models, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also compares the performance of different models, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates the models' performance on different test settings, which relates to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
